TITLE: Handling Errors in JSON:API Requests with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates error handling with try/catch for API requests. Errors thrown by the Fetch handler include additional properties like parsed error content, status codes, and normalized error information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emberjs/data/blob/main/guides/requests/examples/0-basic-usage.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { query } from '@ember-data/json-api/request';
import fetch from './fetch';

// ... execute a request
try {
  const result = await fetch.request(query('company', {
    include: ['ceo'],
    fields: {
      company: 'name',
      employee: ['name', 'profileImage']
    },
    page: {
      size: 10
    }
  }));
} catch (error) {
  // errors will be normal Errors with some extra information
  error instanceof Error; // true

  // request and response are also available on errors
  const { request, response } = error;
}
```

