TITLE: Implementing Error Handling in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates error handling in a request handler, including retrying on timeout errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/emberjs/data/blob/main/packages/request/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const MAX_RETRIES = 5;

const Handler = {
  async request(context, next) {
    let attempts = 0;

    while (attempts < MAX_RETRIES) {
      attempts++;
      try {
        const response = await next(context.request);
        return response;
      } catch (e) {
        if (isTimeoutError(e) && attempts < MAX_RETRIES) {
          // retry request
          continue;
        }
        // rethrow if it is not a timeout error
        throw e;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

